    "narrative": "The primary engine for Ghost Ride the WHIP today is **Mickey Moniak**, who carries our highest efficiency score of 75.75. Facing the vulnerable R. V\u00e1squez, **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive 19% boost due to the favorable SP matchup and a 14% cushion from a dynamic platoon advantage, making him a cornerstone of the lineup despite a slight park penalty. Right behind him, **Jose Caballero** (72.91) serves as our primary speed anchor. While he is relegated to the eight-hole, his elite sprint speed paired with a slow delivery from the opposing pitcher creates a high-probability environment for stolen bases, a scarcity-driven metric we prioritize heavily. **Giancarlo Stanton** also provides significant muscle at 68.81, leveraging a favorable matchup against the left-handed Springs to anchor our power production.\n\nThe most difficult decision of the day involved **Max Muncy** (59.95) versus our bench options. **Max Muncy** narrowly edged out the competition because his matchup against Weathers checks every box: he avoids the platoon penalty and benefits from the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, which keeps our SB-hungry team competitive even with a power-first bat. While **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** possesses superior raw speed, he remains benched due to a lack of confirmed lineup status, rendering his efficiency moot for today\u2019s cap management. We are also monitoring **Vinnie Pasquantino** (53.94) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (55.94) closely; both face a lingering platoon risk against lefties, though **Vinnie Pasquantino**'s wind-aided park boost keeps him firmly in the marginal start category. \n\nWe are currently navigating a thin bench, with **Corbin Carroll**, **Josh Naylor**, and **James Wood** all unavailable for various rest or scheduling reasons. The lack of depth is being compensated by the consistent deployment of **Zach McKinstry** (48.81), whose matchup against Abel provides just enough statistical utility to justify his inclusion over leaving the slot empty. We continue to hold **Austin Riley**, **Seiya Suzuki**, **Trevor Story**, **Brice Turang**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, **Kyle Karros**, **Carson Williams**, **Gabriel Arias**, and **Travis Bazzana** in reserve, keeping an eye on future matchups that align better with our efficiency-first strategy. For now, we are banking on the high-floor outcomes of **Mickey Moniak** and **Jose Caballero** to carry the weight while we avoid the volatility of suboptimal platoons elsewhere.",
